==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blacksnake
<hw>Black"snake</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
snake of a black color, of which two species are common in the United
States, the <spn>Bascanium constrictor</spn>, or racer, sometimes six
feet long, and the <spn>Scotophis Alleghaniensis</spn>, seven or eight
feet long.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is also applied to various other black
serpents, as <spn>Natrix atra</spn> of Jamaica.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Black Spanish</ent>⟦br⟧
